The paper focuses on the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for material classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of Support Vector Machines (SVMs) and transfer learning, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The evaluation of different CNN architectures and the analysis of results can also fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
